# New Joiners Guide

When a new team member joins, follow this guide, and log completion in a ticket.  

Your line manager should have: 

- Requested your Dom1 account (@justice.gov.uk account) 
- Ordered your MacBook / other relevant kit 
- Requested a Slack account 

## Slack

Once a Slack account has been created you will need to be added to the Cloud Optimisation and Accountability Slack Channels.

Add new team members to `#cloud-optimisation-and-accountability-team`, `#coat-notifications`, `#finops-greenops-community`, `#green-software` and `#analytical-platform-support`.

## Cloud Optimisation and Accountability Site 

This [site](https://cloud-optimisation-and-accountability.justice.gov.uk/) explains our tools, services, and processes, including our team vision, how we work, our services, code, and runbooks.

## Github Account

Setup a new account on [GitHub](https://github.com/) using your @justice.gov.uk email address. 

## MoJ Github

Runbook: [Add user to GitHub](https://runbooks.operations-engineering.service.justice.gov.uk/documentation/services/github/add-github-user.html)

After the invitation has been accepted, check access to the [Ministry of Justice organisation](https://github.com/ministryofjustice) and the [moj-analytical-services organisation](https://github.com/orgs/moj-analytical-services).

Join the cloud-optimisation-and-accountability team in the Ministry of Justice organisation. 

## Access to project board(s)

We use the [Cloud Optimisation and Accountability Team GitHub Project](https://github.com/orgs/ministryofjustice/projects/52) to manage our workflow.

## Access to Miro

Request a Miro account on [Service Now](https://mojprod.service-now.com/moj_sp?id=sc_cat_item&sys_id=550b40b31b7aa018f58d206fe54bcb80&table=sc_cat_item&searchTerm=miro). 

Go to [Miro](https://miro.com/) and sign in using your Justice account. Join the [team’s project board](https://miro.com/app/board/o9J_lsgfhYk=/). You must have an MoJ license to access this.  

## AWS (COAT Development and COAT Production) 

[SSO using GitHub](https://moj.awsapps.com/start)

## Microsoft Group  

A team member will add you to our existing Cloud Optimisation and Accountability Team MS Group.  

This will give you access to: 

- COAT team calendar (you will need to add this in Outlook browser) 
- COAT MS Teams Group 
- COAT SharePoint 

You will also need to request access to our mailbox. You will need to do this via a Service Now request using the [Shared Mailbox – Maintain](https://mojprod.service-now.com/moj_sp?id=sc_cat_item&table=sc_cat_item&sys_id=f375ef4edb73e7441b4ffc45ae9619cd&recordUrl=com.glideapp.servicecatalog_cat_item_view.do%3Fv%3D1&sysparm_id=f375ef4edb73e7441b4ffc45ae9619cd) option. You must request ‘Full Access with send on behalf of’ for <cloudoptimisationandaccountabilityteam@justice.gov.uk>.  







